# Blueberry Lemon Scones

> Adapted from [this recipe](https://www.foodnetwork.com/recipes/tyler-florence/blueberry-scones-with-lemon-glaze-recipe-1914780) and [this recipe](https://www.simplyrecipes.com/recipes/lemon_blueberry_scones/)

## Ingredients 
Blueberry Scones:
* 2 cups all-purpose flour
* 1 tablespoon baking powder
* 1/2 teaspoon kosher salt
* 2 tablespoons granulated sugar
* 5 tablespoons unsalted butter, cold
* 1 cup fresh blueberries
* 1 cup heavy cream

Lemon Glaze:
* zest from 1 medium lemon
* 2 tablespoons lemon juice from 1 medium lemon
* 1 1/2 cups confectioners' sugar

## Directions
1. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper
1. Sift together the dry ingredients into a bowl: flour, baking powder, salt, and sugar
1. Shred the butter and mix into the dry ingredients until the mixture resembles course crumbs
1. Fold the blueberries into the batter. Do not mash or bruise the blueberries
1. Make a well in the center of the bowl and pour in the heavy cream
1. Fold in cream just to incorporate, do not overmix
1. Press the dough out on a lightly floured surface into a large disk, about 1 1/4 inches thick
1. Cut the dough disk into wedges and place on the baking sheet
1. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes until lightly browned
1. While the scones are baking, make the glaze by whisking together the lemon zest, lemon juice and confectioners' sugar in a small bowl
1. Add additional lemon juice or confectioners' sugar to achieve a pourable consistency
1. Transfer the entire parchment paper with the scones onto a cooling track
1. While the scones are still warm, drizzle each scone with a spoonful of lemon glaze
1. Allow glaze to set before serving
